---
import SupportPage from '../../components/SupportPage.astro';
---
<SupportPage
  locale="en"
  path="/support/faq.html"
  title="FAQ | GYUTRON Support"
  description="Frequently asked questions about GYUTRON industrial hardware — products, interfaces, customization, samples, lead times, certifications, integration support, shipping and warranty."
  eyebrow="Help & Support"
  heading="Frequently Asked Questions"
  crumb="FAQ"
  intro="Answers to the questions we hear most often from manufacturers, system integrators and B2B buyers."
>
  <div class="support-faq">
    <details>
      <summary>What products does GYUTRON offer?</summary>
      <p>GYUTRON supplies industrial intelligent hardware: machine-vision and code-reading cameras, smart vision sensors, proximity and environmental sensors, rugged Android PDAs and RFID handhelds, barcode scanners, dimensional gauges and measurement instruments, plus related automation components — for global manufacturers and system integrators.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do you offer OEM / ODM and customization?</summary>
      <p>Yes. For qualified volume programs we support custom configurations, firmware, housings, connectors and private labeling. Share your specification and target quantity with our sales engineering team to scope a solution.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Which interfaces and protocols are supported?</summary>
      <p>Depending on the product line: GigE Vision, USB3, RS-232/485, IO-Link and digital I/O for vision and sensing devices; Android-based rugged handhelds with Wi-Fi, cellular and Bluetooth. Devices integrate via standard SDKs and common industrial protocols. Exact interfaces are listed on each product datasheet.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Can I request a sample or evaluation unit?</summary>
      <p>Evaluation units are available for qualified projects. Tell us about your application, interface and expected volume through <a href="/contact-sales.html">Contact Sales</a> and we will advise on availability.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>What are typical lead times?</summary>
      <p>In-stock items ship promptly; configured or made-to-order items depend on the options and quantity. Confirmed lead times are provided with each quotation.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do you provide SDKs, drivers and integration support?</summary>
      <p>Yes. We provide the SDKs and drivers required for integration and offer application-engineering assistance to help you bring a device into your platform or line.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>What certifications do your products carry?</summary>
      <p>Depending on the model, products may carry CE, FCC and RoHS, and use IP-rated housings (for example IP65 / IP67) for industrial environments. Specific certifications and ratings are stated on each product datasheet.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How do I get a quotation?</summary>
      <p>Send the product model(s), quantity and target date through <a href="/contact-sales.html">Contact Sales</a>, and our team will prepare a quotation.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do you ship internationally?</summary>
      <p>Yes — we ship worldwide from Hong Kong and Shenzhen. See <a href="/support/shipping-delivery.html">Shipping &amp; Delivery</a> for incoterms, customs and lead-time details.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>What warranty do you provide?</summary>
      <p>GYUTRON hardware carries a limited warranty against defects in materials and workmanship. See the <a href="/support/warranty.html">Warranty</a> page for coverage, exclusions and the RMA process.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Where do I get datasheets, firmware and manuals?</summary>
      <p>Contact your sales engineer or <a href="mailto:info@gyutron.com">info@gyutron.com</a> for documentation, firmware and manuals. A self-service Downloads area is being expanded.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do you offer after-sales service and repair?</summary>
      <p>Yes. After-sales service and repair are handled through our RMA process — start by <a href="/support.html">contacting support</a> with the product model, serial number and a description of the issue.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</SupportPage>
